\\\\
&=4x-3x^{-1}+x^{-2}
\end{align}$

### Differentiating using the power rule

$\begin{align}
&\phantom{=}\dfrac{d}{dx}(4x-3x^{-1}+x^{-2})
\\\\
&=4\dfrac{d}{dx}(x)-3\dfrac{d}{dx}(x^{-1})+\dfrac{d}{dx}(x^{-2})
\\\\
&=4 (1x^0)-3(-1)x^{-2}+(-2)x^{-3}
\\\\
&=4+3x^{-2}-2x^{-3}
\\\\
&=4+\dfrac{3}{x^2}-\dfrac{2}{x^3}
\end{align}$

